foia:ProcessedAppealSection.foia:FootnoteText: Concerning all tables in Section VI, not all components process administrative appeals. OSD/JS FOIA Appeals Branch processes the following components’ appeals: AFRICOM, CENTCOM, DoDEA, DTIC, EUCOM, JFCOM, NGB, NORTHCOM, OSD/JS, PACOM, SOCOM, SOUTHCOM, STRATCOM, TRANSCOM, and TRICARE.

Column one should be the same number as the number of pending FOIA requests reported by each component at the end of FY09. The differences in numbers for AF, DIA, NGA, NRO and OSD/JS are due to better accounting methods which caused some minor discrepancy in starting numbers.

foia:AppealDispositionSection.foia:FootnoteText: ABSCA, DeCA and DSS did not process any appeals in FY10.

foia:AppealResponseTimeSection.foia:FootnoteText: Due to the decentralized processing and tracking of FOIA requests within the DoD and because the DoD does not have the means to centrally capture all the required data, it is not possible to calculate DoD (Agency) medians. Furthermore, Army has multiple reporting components and is not able to compute medians for its overall totals.
ABSCA, DeCA, DSS and DTRA did not process any appeals in FY10

foia:ProcessedResponseTimeSection.foia:FootnoteText: Due to the decentralized processing and tracking of FOIA requests within the DoD and because the DoD does not have the means to centrally capture all the required data, it is not possible to calculate DoD (Agency) medians. Furthermore, Army has multiple reporting components and was not able to compute medians for its overall totals. This applies to all tables with medians in Section VII.

foia:ExpeditedProcessingSection.foia:FootnoteText: Due to the decentralized processing and tracking of FOIA requests within the DoD and because the DoD does not have the means to centrally capture all the required data, it is not possible to calculate DoD medians and the medians for some components that have more than one FOIA requester service center.

foia:FeeWaiverSection.foia:FootnoteText: Due to the decentralized processing and tracking of FOIA requests within the DoD and because the DoD does not have the means to centrally capture all the required data, it is not possible to calculate DoD medians and the medians for some components that have more than one FOIA requester service center.

foia:BacklogSection.foia:FootnoteText: Not all components process administrative appeals. OSD/JS FOIA Appeals Branch processes the following components’ appeals: AFRICOM, CENTCOM, DoDEA, DTIC, EUCOM, NGB, NORTHCOM, PACOM, SOCOM, SOUTHCOM, TRANSCOM, and TRICARE.

foia:ProcessedConsultationSection.foia:FootnoteText: The numbers in this column should equal the numbers reported in the previous year’s report.
